This restaurant is only 2 minutes away from where I live. I do like the food and it has been one of my to go places for the past years. Unfortunately  they recently hired a new lady who has made me not want to visit the restaurant anymore. She does not have any type of professionalism, has a horrible attitude with customers and does not seem to know what the menu consist of. Seems as if she is super exhausted when speaking to customers and will literally diminish the amount of clientele by telling them certain foods are not available when another employee tells her the food is available they will just need to wait a little longer for food to be prepared. I am very easy going and definitely do not enjoy complaining to anyone specially to someone making my food. Writing a review was the best option for me. I will say this is poor management not so much the employees fault. The owner will have to train or perhaps look over their employees more often as this can bring a business down.

First off this review is based on the location of Q'kachapa at this address:  5625 Broadway Bronx, NY 10463 ‎  I started checking this place out this month for the lack of authentic latin food Riverdale offers. I started simple since all the food looked delicious. I have been ordering the taco supreme for quite sometime. I would have made this a very good review, but the one thing that kills this review is this:  the customer service.  I ordered a taco supreme, but I just wanted the kid to just hold off on the guacamole. At first he did not seem to understand, so I ask him again if he can hold of on the guacamole .He then suggests if I wanted it to put the guacamole on the side (meaning put it in a plastic container to put it where I like.), I say okay just as long as it is not on the taco. So I wait, I get my dish and I am on my way back. The second I actually look at my dish trusting that was not what I think I saw, there it was, guacamole.  It's surprising how the little things can really get on a persons nerves. Overall, they have a incredible menu from Venezuelan food to american chili fries, all with cheese burgers with a good touch of Mexican cuisine, but what good is going there if you can not ask to hold back on certain part of your food. I am the customer, I am the one paying here!  I really, really, really wanted to like this place, but if I can't even get one simple request to be done then I will just try to find a Chipotle. At least the cashier will give me the common decency of their attention.
